Germany Begins Women’s World Cup Soccer Title Defense With Win Over Canada

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-06-26T18:22:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-26/germany-begins-women-s-world-cup-soccer-title-defense-with-win-over-canada.html
Germany  opened the defense of its
Women’s World Cup soccer title with a 2-1 win against Canada.
France defeated Nigeria 1-0 in the other match on the first day
of the tournament.  Kerstin Garefrekes and Celia Okoyino da Mbabi scored in
Berlin for host nation Germany, which has won the past two
editions of the four-yearly event. Christine Sinclair scored
with a late free kick for Canada.  Group A leader Germany and France each have three points
after a Marie-Laure Delie goal in Sinsheim decided the other
match.  The 16 teams are split into four groups with the top two in
each progressing to the quarterfinals. The final of the four-
yearly  soccer tournament  is on July 17.  Tomorrow, Japan plays New Zealand, while Mexico faces
England in the opening matches of Group B.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 James Cone  in London at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 